TEXT.P:
The protected species are: broad-tailed swallowtail butterfly;
highland red-bellied swallowtail butterfly; bird-winged butterfly;
Heng-chun bird-winged butterfly; large purple fritillary; Formosan
giant cicada; Watanabei's lanternfly; jumbo dragonfly; brilliant
jewel beetle; rainbow sheath click beetle; Formosan long-armed
scarab; Formosan giant stag beetle; Formosan long-fanged stag beetle;
Wu-she blood-spotted longhorn beetle; Formosan snail-eating ground
beetle; Lan-hsu giant katydid; and big-headed stick insect, said COA
officials.

DOC.TEXT:
The lead stories in major Taiwan dailies on
Sunday are as follows:

@The Central Daily News: List of cross-party task force unveiled.

@The China Times: President says no to construction of Meinung
Dam, promises to improve the quality of Kaohsiung's tap water and to
transfer the administration of Kaohsiung Harbor to Kaohsiung City.

@The United Daily News: Requirements for applying for prime
mortgaged loans relaxed.

@The Liberty Times: President says Meinung Dam will not be built
during his term in office.

@The China Post: Chen pledges better water.

@The Taiwan News: Chen says he won't allow Meinung Reservoir to
be built.

@The Taipei Times: President Chen shelves Meinung Dam project.

