Wu said she believed life is a continuous education, adding that
while she has learned to be dutiful, handle pain, and serve others,
she still has to learn to abandon fame and wealth.

The price indexes for the eight major categories all closed
lower, with electrical and electronics issues registering a 2 percent
drop; cement issues, down 0.4 percent; plastics, down 1.4 percent;
textiles, down 1.5 percent; construction, down 2.5 percent; financial
and banking stocks, down 1.1 percent; foodstuff, down 0.4 percent;
and pulp and paper, down 0.1 percent.

-- The Republic of China has been an independent sovereign state
since its establishment in 1912; this is an indisputable fact;
although the two sides remain divided over the definition of "one
China," all parties (including the international community) must
respect the "status quo" on both sides of the Taiwan Strait;

-- Either side of the Taiwan Strait now has a legitimate
government that exercises effective jurisdiction within its scope;
and each side has its own rights and obligations concerning
international affairs;

-- The two sides should adopt confidence and security building
measures, promote regular security dialogue and develop a direct
dialogue mechanism to avoid misjudgment of the situation;

-- The two sides jointly set up an elite forum to pool wisdom of
experts and scholars on both sides to work out feasible measures to
ensure peaceful development of cross-strait ties;

-- Mainland China provides incentives and necessary protection
to attract Taiwan investors to help develop mainland China's less
developed inland areas;

-- Strengthening national defense and diplomacy, promoting
resumption of dialogue between the two sides of the Taiwan Strait
and ensuring national security;

-- Accelerating government re-engineering and restructuring and
developing a partnership with all local people based on trust and
